    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Seven credibility factors assessed; six of seven meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. The discretization error factor achieved Gradation 1 against a required Gradation 2; however, the assessment team judged that the 6.8% GCI on the fine mesh is marginally above threshold and that the overall pattern of validation evidence across the remaining six factors provides sufficient confidence for the intended regulatory submission. Decision accepted pending corrective re-mesh action item prior to final 510(k) filing.",
